e. I wonder how to handle this!\\\"},{\\\"type\\\":\\\"summary_text\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Considering UrlFormLifter issues**\\\\n\\\\nI wonder if `UrlFormLifter` is unsupported with the native image due to a Scala 3/JDK 25 bug. I can't skip any instructions here. How can I avoid adding source code that causes this bug while still keeping functional coverage? Perhaps I could remove the `UrlFormLifter` test, but I need to maintain that coverage. There was an initial test in version 0.23, and the user seems to want runtime failures rather than just metadata. This is a tricky situation!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_aBG7lGnR3STLV2LXVTNTUKw3|fc_01dabda23fd64c9e016a23a005440c81908f8b99493596d28b\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find metadata/org.http4s/http4s-server_3/1.0.0-M22 -type f -maxdepth 3 -print | xargs -r grep -n \\\"lambda\\\\|allDeclared\\\\|queryAll\\\" | head -50\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 912, \"output\": 762, \"cacheRead\": 70144, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 71818, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1780719601925, \"responseId\": \"resp_01dabda23fd64c9e016a239ff28a888190bb0844c4d829cef3\"}, \"toolResults\": [{\"role\": \"toolResult\", \"toolCallId\": \"call_aBG7lGnR3STLV2LXVTNTUKw3|fc_01dabda23fd64c9e016a23a005440c81908f8b99493596d28b\", \"toolName\": \"bash\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"(no output)\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1780719622683}]}\n2449:[thinking] I'm thinking about using `javap -v Entity` to inspect class files, but maybe that's not the right approach. Instead, I could run `javap -c` on the UrlFormLifter class from the jar. First, I just need to locate that jar file, and it might be helpful to use the cache for that. It’s a bit of back and forth, but I’m figurin